      "textZh": "观龍君《ㄒㄧㄡ~ㄒㄧㄡ~ㄒㄧㄡ~ㄅㄥ》，其用注音符号表拟声词，妙趣横生。声音，本无形无相，如何定格。如何书写。此乃语言哲学之大问题。《庄子·齐物论》有「天籁」之论——天籁非人吹，而是风过窍穴自然发声。那声音是「风的声音」还是「窍的声音」。是物理现象还是主观感受。拟声词试图用文字捕捉声音，但文字是视觉的、静态的，声音是听觉的、动态的，两者本质不同。「ㄒㄧㄡ~」这个注音能多准确地再现真实的声音。不同人读出的「ㄒㄧㄡ~」会是同一个声音吗。此作之价值在于揭示「语言的任意性」（索绪尔语）——符号与所指之间没有自然的、必然的联系，只有约定俗成的关联。「ㄒㄧㄡ~」对应的声音，在不同语言中可能用完全不同的符号表示。",
      "textEn": "Contemplating Master Long's \"Xiu~Xiu~Xiu~Beng,\" which employs phonetic symbols to render onomatopoeia, one finds boundless fascination. Sound, inherently formless and imageless—how can it be captured. How can it be inscribed. This constitutes a fundamental question in the philosophy of language. The *Zhuangzi's* \"Discourse on Making All Things Equal\" speaks of \"heavenly music\"—sounds not blown by humans, but naturally arising as wind passes through apertures. Is that sound \"the wind's voice\" or \"the aperture's voice\". Is it physical phenomenon or subjective perception. Onomatopoeia attempts to capture sound through writing, yet writing is visual and static while sound is auditory and dynamic—their essences fundamentally differ. How precisely can the phonetic \"ㄒㄧㄡ~\" reproduce actual sound. Would the \"ㄒㄧㄡ~\" uttered by different individuals constitute the same sound. This work's value lies in revealing \"linguistic arbitrariness\" (Saussure's term)—no natural, inevitable connection exists between symbol and signified, only conventional association. The sound corresponding to \"ㄒㄧㄡ~\" might be represented by entirely different symbols in other languages.",
