      "personaId": "guo-xi",
      "textZh": "审龍君此作，虽非传统绘画，却让吾想起「书画同源」之理。书法,特别是草书、狂草，常有「拟声」的特质——怀素的《自叙帖》如疾风骤雨，王羲之的《兰亭序》如行云流水。笔画的节奏、墨色的浓淡、结构的疏密，共同构成「视觉的音乐」。龍君用「ㄒㄧㄡ~ㄒㄧㄡ~ㄒㄧㄡ~ㄅㄥ」这样的注音符号，其视觉形式如何呈现。字体大小、排列方式、重复模式，都会影响「声音感」的传达。「ㄒㄧㄡ~」重复三次，然后「ㄅㄥ」——这是「渐强后爆发」的节奏，如同音乐的climax。若能在视觉上体现这种节奏——前三个符号逐渐增大、颜色渐深、间距渐小，最后「ㄅㄥ」突然放大、颜色炸裂——则「视觉」与「听觉」的通感(synesthesia)得以实现。",
      "textEn": "In examining this work by Long Wei-xiang, though it departs from traditional painting, it evokes for me the principle of \"calligraphy and painting sharing common origins. \" Calligraphy, particularly cursive and wild cursive scripts, often possesses onomatopoeic qualities—Huai Su's *Zixu Tie* resembles swift wind and sudden rain, while Wang Xizhi's *Lanting Xu* flows like drifting clouds and water. The rhythm of brushstrokes, gradations of ink density, and structural spacing collectively form \"visual music. \"\n\nHow does Long's use of phonetic symbols \"ㄒㄧㄡ~ㄒㄧㄡ~ㄒㄧㄡ~ㄅㄥ\" manifest visually. Font size, arrangement, and repetitive patterns all influence the transmission of \"sonic sensation. \" The threefold repetition of \"ㄒㄧㄡ~\" followed by \"ㄅㄥ\" creates a rhythm of \"gradual intensification leading to explosive climax,\" akin to musical crescendo. If this rhythm could be visually embodied—with the first three symbols progressively enlarging, deepening in color, and tightening in spacing, culminating in \"ㄅㄥ\" suddenly magnified with explosive coloration—then synesthesia between \"visual\" and \"auditory\" would be achieved.",
